\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Methods\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Study Design and Ethical Considerations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 This cross-sectional clinical study was conducted between March 2023 and February 2024 at a university-affiliated medical center. The study protocol was approved by the institutional ethics committee, and all participants provided written informed consent prior to participation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Participants\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 A total of 260 adults aged 20\'9660 years were recruited through community advertisements and outpatient clinics. Inclusion criteria included the ability to provide informed consent and no antibiotic use within the preceding three months. Exclusion criteria included inflammatory bowel disease, chronic gastrointestinal disorders, pregnancy, current substance use disorder, severe psychiatric illness other than depression, and use of probiotic or prebiotic supplements within four weeks prior to enrollment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

