\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Statistical Analysis\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Continuous variables were expressed as mean \'b1 standard deviation, and categorical variables as frequencies and percentages. Group comparisons were conducted using analysis of variance or chi-square tests as appropriate. Multivariate linear regression models were used to assess the association between microbiome diversity metrics and PHQ-9 scores. Statistical significance was defined as p < 0.05.\
