\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Results\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Participant Characteristics\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Of the 260 participants, 248 provided complete clinical and microbiome data. The mean age was 38.4 \'b1 10.7 years, and 55% were female. Thirty-four percent of participants met criteria for moderate to severe depressive symptoms (PHQ-9 \uc0\u8805 10).\
Baseline demographic and lifestyle characteristics were similar across depression severity groups, although participants with higher PHQ-9 scores reported lower physical activity levels and higher perceived stress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Gut Microbiome Diversity\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Alpha diversity was significantly lower in participants with moderate to severe depressive symptoms compared to those with minimal symptoms. Mean Shannon index values were 3.1 \'b1 0.5 in the moderate/severe group versus 3.8 \'b1 0.6 in the minimal symptom group (p < 0.001).\
Beta diversity analysis demonstrated distinct clustering of microbial communities based on depressive symptom severity, indicating differences in overall microbiome composition.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Taxonomic Differences\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Participants with higher PHQ-9 scores exhibited reduced relative abundance of butyrate-producing genera, including 
\f2\i Faecalibacterium
\f0\i0 , 
\f2\i Roseburia
\f0\i0 , and 
\f2\i Eubacterium
\f0\i0 . Increased abundance of potentially pro-inflammatory genera, such as 
\f2\i Escherichia/Shigella
\f0\i0 , was observed in participants with more severe depressive symptoms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Multivariate Analysis\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 After adjusting for age, sex, BMI, diet quality, physical activity, antidepressant use, and stress, lower gut microbiome alpha diversity remained independently associated with higher PHQ-9 scores (\uc0\u946  = \u8722 0.42, p < 0.001).\
